defs.docs:
Crossbeam supports concurrent programming, especially focusing on memory
 management, synchronization, and non-blocking data structures.

defs.name: ArcCell
defs.docs: A type providing atomic storage and retrieval of an `Arc<T>`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `ArcCell`.

defs.name: set
defs.docs:
Stores a new value in the `ArcCell`, returning the previous
 value.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns a copy of the value stored by the `ArcCell`.

defs.name: atomic
defs.docs: Additional utilities for atomics.

defs.name: utils
defs.docs: Utilities for concurrent programming.

defs.name: MsQueue
defs.docs: A Michael-Scott lock-free queue, with support for blocking `pop`s.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new, empty queue.

defs.name: push
defs.docs:
Add `t` to the back of the queue, possibly waking up threads
 blocked on `pop`.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Check if this queue is empty.

defs.name: try_pop
defs.docs: Attempt to dequeue from the front.

defs.name: pop
defs.docs:
Dequeue an element from the front of the queue, blocking if the queue is
 empty.

defs.name: SegQueue
defs.docs:
A Michael-Scott queue that allocates "segments" (arrays of nodes)
 for efficiency.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new, empty queue.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Add `t` to the back of the queue.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Judge if the queue is empty.

defs.name: try_pop
defs.docs: Attempt to dequeue from the front.

defs.name: ShardedLock
defs.docs: A scalable reader-writer lock.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `ShardedLock` initialized with `value`.

defs.name: read
defs.docs: Locks with shared read access, blocking the current thread until it can be acquired.

defs.name: write
defs.docs: Locks with exclusive write access, blocking the current thread until it can be acquired.

defs.name: ShardedLockReadGuard
defs.docs: A guard used to release the shared read access of a `ShardedLock` when dropped.

defs.name: ShardedLockWriteGuard
defs.docs: A guard used to release the exclusive write access of a `ShardedLock` when dropped.

defs.name: TreiberStack
defs.docs: Treiber's lock-free stack.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new, empty stack.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Push `t` on top of the stack.

defs.name: try_pop
defs.docs: Attempt to pop the top element of the stack.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Check if this queue is empty.

defs.name: WaitGroup
defs.docs: Enables multiple threads to synchronize the beginning or end of some computation.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new wait group and returns the single reference to it.

defs.name: wait
defs.docs: Drops this reference and waits until all other references are dropped.

defs.name: queue
defs.docs: Concurrent queues.

defs.name: stack
defs.docs: Concurrent stacks.

defs.name: sync
defs.docs: Utilities for thread synchronization.
